34: Alk... Alk... Can you hear me?
42:
Listen. I'm gonna draw their
attention. You look for a chance to—
52:
You've got to protect the others!
That's what you promised to do,
remember?
56:
Don't you worry about me. I ain't
givin' up the ghost yet—just like
everyone else back home! Trust me,
partner!
59:
'Sides... You've got a better chance
of knocking sense into that bastard's
skull anyway.
104:
Bring it on! Crushing you and
everything you stand for is only
gonna make me STRONGER!
107:
I'll take as many of you down as I
have to, and then some!
114:
Ain't nothing gonna stop me—or the
crazy fools that jumped in here with
me!
144:
Using lingering emotions as a
medium to alter reality... To develop
a soul is one thing, but the ability to
fight back? You're full of surprises...
147:
But, I'm the one who is connected to
the dragon.
159: Why... are you doing this, Nova?
163: You did the same thing, didn't you?
166:
You broke and gained a soul, only to
try and discard it.
169:
But for us, it was impossible. Not
without the spear. All we could do
was keep making them...
176:
New versions of ourselves. Every
time we broke, another was created.
It was all we could do in the Void.
179:
I told you already—I'm nothing more
than a husk. There are countless
more versions of me in here.
183:
But now, I'll get rid of them all... Don't
you dare try to stop me!
225:
The dragon can no longer see this
world. Only we, created from the
Origin, have the power to change
reality here.
229:
You can't stop this. You're too late,
Alk. You've always been too late!
238:
The past can't be unwritten. We can
never return to who we were when
we met in that park.
252:
Yes... One of the Origin's memories. A
past that curses us but can't be
erased.
261:
How long do you intend to keep up
this farce?
264:
You know the truth about why the
two of you were split, even if you
pretend not to...
275:
You were never abandoned. You
chose to leave. And you still weren't
satisfied.
278:
You ran away from fate—from your
own sins. You've lied to yourself all
this time, burdened by a curse
greater than the rest.
290:
You wanted to share in the same
dream as everyone else, didn't you?
To become just like them, no matter
how rotten you were inside and out.
292:
If that's what you desire... consider
your wish granted.
308:
Pierce flesh... and mend them as
one!
